// Triết-in-Triết typechecker port — bootstrap source for the
// self-hosting compiler ([ADR-0019][adr-0019] §A7.7 v0.7.7
// umbrella).
//
// v0.7.7.1 — Types + TypeError + Env scaffolding. Mirrors
// crates/triet-typecheck/src/{types.rs, error.rs, env.rs}:
// declares the resolved-type representation, the 27-variant
// `TypeError` enum (E1001 → E1034 + W2001), and the scoped
// `TypeEnvironment` (frame stack + Binding) that subsequent
// v0.7.7.{2..4} sub-tasks will populate from `check_resolved`.
//
// Types coverage:
//   - `TypeKind` (semantic types) — 16 variants covering primitives
//     (Trit / Tryte / Integer / Long / Trilean / String / Unit),
//     recursive wrappers (Nullable / Tuple / Function / Range /
//     Outcome), user-defined (Struct / Enum), generic-param slots
//     (TypeParam), and the recovery placeholder (Unknown).
//   - `TypeArena` — `Vector<TypeNode>` keyed by Integer ID. Mirrors
//     compiler/parser/parser.tri's Arena: Triết enum variants
//     can't recursively contain themselves (no `Box<Self>`), so
//     every `Box<Type>` field becomes an arena ID. `alloc_type` +
//     `get_type` are the read/write API.
//   - `TypeError` (27 variants) — E1001 UnknownType through E1034
//     TrileanReturnNotRefined + W2001 NullDeprecated. Per-variant
//     payload struct pattern (matches modules.tri's LoaderError).
//   - `TypeEnvironment` — Vector<Frame> scope stack + per-frame
//     `HashMap<String, Binding>`. `Binding` carries arena type id
//     + mutable flag.
//
// v0.7.7.1 is types-only: no `check_*` driver yet. Smoke main
// exercises construction + display + Env push/pop/lookup so the
// integration test (`typecheck_types_smoke.rs`) can confirm the
// surface compiles + round-trips through the VM. v0.7.7.{2..5}
// build the actual checker on this foundation.
//
// [adr-0019]: ../docs/decisions/0019-self-hosting-compiler-bootstrap.md

module parser;
module modules;

